{"runId":"run-scaffold-astro-starlight-site-first-slice-bones-a9716b","taskId":"task-build-43b320","eventType":"gate.decided","ts":"2026-06-03T17:47:21.320Z","payload":{"decision":"reject","rationale":"Build wave produced a non-persisted scaffold. The agentic-platform-builder child (task-build-0-933a91) wrote all 15 scaffold files cwd-relative into the container's ephemeral /workspace instead of the /project bind mount, so the entire Astro+Starlight scaffold (package.json, astro.config.mjs, src/styles/tokens.css, vercel.json, content config, node_modules, dist) was discarded on container exit despite result.json reporting status:complete with a passing pnpm build. Host has zero of those files. The sibling frontend-specialist files that DID persist (MarketingLayout.astro + two marketing pages) are dangling — they import ../styles/global.css and reference 36 --forge-* design tokens that lived only in the discarded scaffold, so the repo does not build. Root cause was a forge container-provisioning bug (cwd defaulted to the image WORKDIR /workspace, not /project); fixed on forge main (commit fb97c69 — buildDockerArgs now passes -w /project) and live in this host's forge (runs from source via tsx, no rebuild needed). Re-dispatching the scaffold now persists correctly. Rejecting to re-run the build step cleanly.","force":false}}
